question.text:
Match the plant with the agent of pollination.
 
Plant Agent of pollination
I. Yucca A. Wind
II. Water Lily B. Water
III. Corn C. Moth
IV. Vallisneria D. Insect

solution.text: Yucca is pollinated by moth in return for a safe place to lay eggs. Water lily is pollinated by either insects or wind as it is an angiosperm and the flowers are above the surface of water. Corn is pollinated by wind. Vallisneria is pollinated by water.
